# Error Handling

## Backend (Python)
- Consistent error envelope: `{ "error": { "code": "...", "message": "...", "details": {} } }`
- Typed exception classes mapping to HTTP status codes. Never raise raw `Exception`.
- Catch at the boundary (route handler). Let exceptions propagate naturally.
- Log errors with context (request ID, tenant ID) at ERROR. Stack traces at DEBUG.
- Never expose internals in API responses.

## Frontend (TypeScript)
- React Error Boundaries for rendering errors. Never crash the host app.
- All async ops must have error handling. No unhandled rejections.
- Network errors: retry with exponential backoff (max 3). Degrade gracefully on failure.
- SDK must be invisible when it fails. No error modals, no console spam.
- Validate all data from backend before rendering.

## Both
- Never swallow errors silently — log or re-throw.
- Error messages must be actionable: what went wrong AND what to do.
- Use error codes for programmatic handling.
